history.text: Hello!
hi!

Have you ever heard of any of these voice actors? I have watched the film but I am just terrible 
with names
Of course. I loved John Goodman as as Mike.
I think he's most famous for playing Dan on Roseanne.
Are the voice actors your favorite part of an animated movie?
Oh cool! Did you like the movie?
nah, i prefer the animation style
Oh. I loved it. I loved the originals Monsters Inc. and it was nice to see how the friendship between Mike and Sully started.
Right? The plot line was so nice. I really liked how they chose to make a prequel!
If your favorite part is the animation, then you must have been a little disappointed. Critics were a little harsh on the animation. What's your favorite animation style, anyways?

Honestly, I dont know! I really don't like claymation though. I also like the stick figure style 
animations
Sully really had a lot of character development! Do you like where they went with it?
Yes. At first he was just this immature frat boy and as the movie progresses we see a lot of growth.
Me too! He became such a good person. Honestly I didn't like him at first, he was so rude and arrogant
I specially liked in the end he was a true friend to Mike.
Yeah! It was such a heartwarming scene. Pixar can really pull those heart strings
It was the first time that Pixar did a prequel on one of its films. I wonder if they'd do more. Are you a fan of prequels in general?
Yeah! Most. SOmetimes they dont do well (like star wars) but they do give some interesting backsotory. It's like expanding the universe
Do you think this was better than the original? Or just an okay film
I think it was better than the first in terms of character development.

For example, o
ne of my favorite parts of the movie is Mike's perseverance in the face of obstacles. Like when he entered the scare games after being kicked out of the scare program.
Yeah! He really showed his commitance to his dreams! It's so strange that the critics gave this film some poor ratings!
I agree!
Like the metacritic store was just 65
The rotten tomatoes was just a 6.8 out of 10
I know! At least Cinimascore gave them an A, they deserved it
Yeah :)
This was also a good underdog story! Do you like those
Yeah. Who doesn't?
True! THey're the best.
Which character was your favorite?

thats a hard question! I really like the Randall in this one. He is just such a hard shift from the last movie
, you know?
what about you?
I liked Mike and Scully, but my favorite was Dean Hardscrabble.
I really liked the way she could instill fear and respect in the students by her mere presence.
The dragon, right?
Yep.
Yeah! Great character, really creepy and just cool in general
Great talk. Bye!
bye!! <3
